Date:  0/0/1889
Source:  Wild West Coast
Author:  PAULINE
Vol / Page:  31
Edition:
Quote:  Maori-head is the name given to a kind of grass which grows in tufts ... often several feet long. It is always found on swampy ground. When the swamp is drained the Maoriheads disappear.
Notes:

