Vol / Page:  285
Edition:
Quote:  <i>Maori-head, n.</i> a swamp tussock, so called from a fancied resemblance to the head of a Maori. (compare <i>Black-boy.</i>) It is not a grass, but a sedge (<i>carex</i>).
